cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MA 

This paper deals with networked control systems, which are typically studied in the control systems community (cs.SY). The paper also involves quantization and information theory concepts, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT. The use of the Lloyd-Max algorithm and Bayesian filtering techniques suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which could place it in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems).
